This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of deep learning techniques for predicting ADMET properties. Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of graph convolutions, which are commonly used in deep learning for graph-based data, further supporting the likelihood of it belonging to cs.LG. 

The paper also discusses the use of cheminformatics approaches, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CE (Chemical Information and Modeling). 

Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and the use of cross-validation procedures, which is a common technique in cs.DB (Databases). 

Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep featurization to enable molecular predictors to extrapolate to new regions of chemical space, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
